#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn74"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn74:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 74 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 74 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn74:0.2"
msgid "Dīghanakhasutta "
msgstr "With Dīghanakha "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli1.498, sc1
msgctxt "mn74:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn74:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate sūkarakhatāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain in the Boar’s Cave. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn74:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho dīghanakho paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then the wanderer Dīghanakha went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "mn74:2.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho dīghanakho paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he stood to one side, and said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "mn74:2.3"
msgid "“ahañhi, bho gotama, evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi: "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, this is my doctrine and view: "

# NOTE: BB has “is acceptable to me”. But this doesn’t quite work. As we see below, the problem is with dogmatic insistence. But to say something is “acceptable” is merely to not rule it out. What’s meant here is closer to the English idea of “belief”.
msgctxt "mn74:2.4"
msgid "‘sabbaṃ me nakkhamatī’”ti. "
msgstr "‘I believe in nothing.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn74:2.5"
msgid "“Yāpi kho te esā, aggivessana, diṭṭhi: "
msgstr "“This view of yours, Aggivessana—"

msgctxt "mn74:2.6"
msgid "‘sabbaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti, esāpi te diṭṭhi nakkhamatī”ti? "
msgstr "do you believe in that?” "

# NOTE: The same idion is found at AN 4.24. Here, I feel the negative form is more natural and comprehensible English.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: ce → esāpi (mr)
msgctxt "mn74:2.7"
msgid "“Esā ce me, bho gotama, diṭṭhi khameyya, taṃpassa tādisameva, taṃpassa tādisamevā”ti. "
msgstr "“If I believed in this view, Master Gotama, it wouldn’t make any difference, it wouldn’t make any difference!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3
msgctxt "mn74:3.1"
msgid "“Ato kho te, aggivessana, bahū hi bahutarā lokasmiṃ ye evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "“Well, Aggivessana, there are many more in the world who say, "

msgctxt "mn74:3.2"
msgid "‘taṃpassa tādisameva, taṃpassa tādisamevā’ti. "
msgstr "‘It wouldn’t make any difference! It wouldn’t make any difference!’ "

msgctxt "mn74:3.3"
msgid "Te tañceva diṭṭhiṃ nappajahanti aññañca diṭṭhiṃ upādiyanti. "
msgstr "But they don’t give up that view, and they grasp another view. "

msgctxt "mn74:3.4"
msgid "Ato kho te, aggivessana, tanū hi tanutarā lokasmiṃ ye evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "And there are a scant few in the world who say, "

msgctxt "mn74:3.5"
msgid "‘taṃpassa tādisameva, taṃpassa tādisamevā’ti. "
msgstr "‘It wouldn’t make any difference! It wouldn’t make any difference!’ "

msgctxt "mn74:3.6"
msgid "Te tañceva diṭṭhiṃ pajahanti aññañca diṭṭhiṃ na upādiyanti. "
msgstr "And they give up that view by not grasping another view. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4
msgctxt "mn74:4.1"
msgid "Santaggivessana, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino: "
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view: "

msgctxt "mn74:4.2"
msgid "‘sabbaṃ me khamatī’ti; "
msgstr "‘I believe in everything.’ "

msgctxt "mn74:4.3"
msgid "santaggivessana, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino: "
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view: "

msgctxt "mn74:4.4"
msgid "‘sabbaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti; "
msgstr "‘I believe in nothing.’ "

msgctxt "mn74:4.5"
msgid "santaggivessana, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino: "
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view: "

msgctxt "mn74:4.6"
msgid "‘ekaccaṃ me khamati, ekaccaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘I believe in some things, and not in others.’ "

msgctxt "mn74:4.7"
msgid "Tatraggivessana, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino: ‘sabbaṃ me khamatī’ti "
msgstr "Regarding this, the view of the ascetics and brahmins who believe in everything "

msgctxt "mn74:4.8"
msgid "tesamayaṃ diṭṭhi sārāgāya santike, saññogāya santike, abhinandanāya santike, ajjhosānāya santike, upādānāya santike; "
msgstr "is close to greed, bondage, approving, attachment, and grasping. "

msgctxt "mn74:4.9"
msgid "tatraggivessana ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino: ‘sabbaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti "
msgstr "The view of the ascetics and brahmins who believe in nothing "

msgctxt "mn74:4.10"
msgid "tesamayaṃ diṭṭhi asārāgāya santike, asaññogāya santike, anabhinandanāya santike, anajjhosānāya santike, anupādānāya santike”ti. "
msgstr "is far from greed, bondage, approving, attachment, and grasping.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, sc2
msgctxt "mn74:5.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, dīghanakho paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, the wanderer Dīghanakha said to the Buddha, "

#. VAR: ukkaṃseti → ukkaṃsati (bj, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: samukkaṃseti → samukkaṃsati (bj, pts1) | sampahaṃsati (mr)
msgctxt "mn74:5.2"
msgid "“ukkaṃseti me bhavaṃ gotamo diṭṭhigataṃ, samukkaṃseti me bhavaṃ gotamo diṭṭhigatan”ti. "
msgstr "“Master Gotama commends my conviction! He recommends my conviction!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.499, sc3
msgctxt "mn74:5.3"
msgid "“Tatraggivessana, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino: "
msgstr "“Now, regarding the ascetics and brahmins who "

msgctxt "mn74:5.4"
msgid "‘ekaccaṃ me khamati, ekaccaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti. "
msgstr "believe in some things and not in others. "

msgctxt "mn74:5.5"
msgid "Yā hi tesaṃ khamati sāyaṃ diṭṭhi sārāgāya santike, saññogāya santike, abhinandanāya santike, ajjhosānāya santike, upādānāya santike; "
msgstr "Their view of what they believe in is close to greed, bondage, approving, attachment, and grasping. "

msgctxt "mn74:5.6"
msgid "yā hi tesaṃ nakkhamati sāyaṃ diṭṭhi asārāgāya santike, asaññogāya santike, anabhinandanāya santike, anajjhosānāya santike, anupādānāya santike. "
msgstr "Their view of what they don’t believe in is far from greed, bondage, approving, attachment, and grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6
msgctxt "mn74:6.1"
msgid "Tatraggivessana, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino: "
msgstr "When it comes to the view of the ascetics and brahmins who "

msgctxt "mn74:6.2"
msgid "‘sabbaṃ me khamatī’ti "
msgstr "believe in everything, "

msgctxt "mn74:6.3"
msgid "tattha viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "a sensible person reflects like this: "

msgctxt "mn74:6.4"
msgid "‘yā kho me ayaṃ diṭṭhi—"
msgstr "‘I have the view that "

msgctxt "mn74:6.5"
msgid "sabbaṃ me khamatīti, "
msgstr "I believe in everything. "

msgctxt "mn74:6.6"
msgid "imañce ahaṃ diṭṭhiṃ thāmasā parāmāsā abhinivissa vohareyyaṃ—"
msgstr "Suppose I obstinately stick to this view and insist that, "

msgctxt "mn74:6.7"
msgid "idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti; "
msgstr "“This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.” "

msgctxt "mn74:6.8"
msgid "dvīhi me assa viggaho—"
msgstr "Then I’d argue with two people—"

msgctxt "mn74:6.9"
msgid "yo cāyaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—sabbaṃ me nakkhamatīti, "
msgstr "an ascetic or brahmin who believes in nothing, "

msgctxt "mn74:6.10"
msgid "yo cāyaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—ekaccaṃ me khamati, ekaccaṃ me nakkhamatīti—"
msgstr "and an ascetic or brahmin who believes in some things and not in others. "

msgctxt "mn74:6.11"
msgid "imehi assa dvīhi viggaho. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn74:6.12"
msgid "Iti viggahe sati vivādo, vivāde sati vighāto, vighāte sati vihesā’. "
msgstr "And when there’s arguing, there’s quarreling; when there’s quarreling there’s anguish; and when there’s anguish there’s harm.’ "

msgctxt "mn74:6.13"
msgid "Iti so viggahañca vivādañca vighātañca vihesañca attani sampassamāno tañceva diṭṭhiṃ pajahati aññañca diṭṭhiṃ na upādiyati. "
msgstr "So, considering in themselves the potential for arguing, quarreling, anguish, and harm, they give up that view by not grasping another view. "

msgctxt "mn74:6.14"
msgid "Evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ pahānaṃ hoti, evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ paṭinissaggo hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how those views are given up and let go. "

